to help me write my resume.

94
00:05:35,297 --> 00:05:36,558
- [Bob] Well, um.

95
00:05:36,558 --> 00:05:38,802
- Maybe we could talk
about it over dinner?

96
00:05:38,802 --> 00:05:39,946
- Dinner?

97
00:05:39,946 --> 00:05:41,718
I, yeah, I'd love to.

98
00:05:41,718 --> 00:05:43,407
- How about tonight?

99
00:05:43,407 --> 00:05:47,553
Pick me up at the 'brask
and Barrington at seven.

100
00:05:47,553 --> 00:05:51,664
- [Bob] Oh, is that the corner
of Nebraska and Barrington?

101
00:05:51,664 --> 00:05:54,826
- That's it. See you at seven.

102
00:05:54,826 --> 00:05:57,326
(upbeat jazz)

103
00:06:23,112 --> 00:06:24,475
- [Norma] Hi.

104
00:06:24,475 --> 00:06:25,308
- Hi.

105
00:06:31,551 --> 00:06:32,384
- Oh.

106
00:06:33,405 --> 00:06:35,738
White roses are my favorite.

107
00:06:36,630 --> 00:06:40,797
Did you know that white roses
were kissed twice by the sun?

108
00:06:44,466 --> 00:06:46,157
You're shy.

109
00:06:46,157 --> 00:06:47,585
That's beautiful.

110
00:06:47,585 --> 00:06:50,694
- Yeah, it's always been
a little bit of a problem.

111
00:06:50,694 --> 00:06:52,361
- I think it's nice.

112
00:07:05,876 --> 00:07:09,376
Do you know what white roses are good for?

113
00:07:13,446 --> 00:07:14,529
Breath mints.

114
00:07:21,791 --> 00:07:24,765
I love driving past these big old houses.

115
00:07:24,765 --> 00:07:27,036
But they're too cold, too dark.

116
00:07:27,036 --> 00:07:29,895
I'd never live here no
matter how much money I make.

117
00:07:29,895 --> 00:07:31,900
- Plan to make a lot of money, do you?

118
00:07:31,900 --> 00:07:34,913
- If they'd ever let me show
them how good I could be.

119
00:07:34,913 --> 00:07:37,094
- They won't let you act now?

120
00:07:37,094 --> 00:07:39,832
- The casting executives
take one look at me

121
00:07:39,832 --> 00:07:43,220
and they see me as a nude model.

122
00:07:43,220 --> 00:07:45,751
Or maybe they see me flat on my back.

123
00:07:45,751 --> 00:07:46,851
(giggles)

124
00:07:46,851 --> 00:07:50,100
- I don't think that's too fun.

125
00:07:50,100 --> 00:07:53,303
- Neither do I but you can't
take life too seriously, right?

126
00:07:53,303 --> 00:07:55,140
- I'm no expert but I think

127
00:07:55,140 --> 00:07:56,450
if you want anything in this life

128
00:07:56,450 --> 00:07:58,232
you've gotta take yourself seriously

129
00:07:58,232 --> 00:07:59,899
or nobody else will.

130
00:08:04,315 --> 00:08:07,369
- I'm so hungry I could eat a mountaintop.

131
00:08:07,369 --> 00:08:08,762
But an actress doesn't work regular,

132
00:08:08,762 --> 00:08:10,361
she doesn't eat regular.

133
00:08:10,361 --> 00:08:11,982
- Writers have the same problem.

134
00:08:11,982 --> 00:08:14,236
- You know, you're the first real writer

135
00:08:14,236 --> 00:08:15,958
I've ever gone out with.

136
00:08:15,958 --> 00:08:17,852
- Well I wouldn't call
writing celebrity stories

137
00:08:17,852 --> 00:08:18,698
being a real writer.

138
00:08:18,698 --> 00:08:20,937
- What do you want to write?

139
00:08:20,937 --> 00:08:22,317
- Movies, mostly.

140
00:08:22,317 --> 00:08:24,206
I've been working on a script for months

141
00:08:24,206 --> 00:08:26,137
that I just can't seem to finish.

142
00:08:26,137 --> 00:08:28,461
I sit down every night and
I look at my typewriter and.

143
00:08:28,461 --> 00:08:29,544
Laughs at me.

144
00:08:31,173 --> 00:08:32,312
- Don't worry.

145
00:08:32,312 --> 00:08:34,383
You'll finish your script soon.

146
00:08:34,383 --> 00:08:36,875
I have faith in you.

147
00:08:36,875 --> 00:08:40,040
Besides, you look like you're doing okay.

148
00:08:40,040 --> 00:08:44,779
- Well I don't want to kid
you, the suit's borrowed.

149
00:08:44,779 --> 00:08:46,897
Have you done much acting?

150
00:08:46,897 --> 00:08:49,255
- Back to my resume?

151
00:08:49,255 --> 00:08:51,877
- That's what I'm here for, isn't it?

152
00:08:51,877 --> 00:08:53,595
- I thought you were here
because you liked me?

153
00:08:53,595 --> 00:08:55,529
- Of course I like you.

154
00:08:55,529 --> 00:08:56,362
- Good.

155
00:08:57,891 --> 00:08:59,141
I like you too.

156
00:09:02,900 --> 00:09:05,849
- You're being very sweet about this.

157
00:09:05,849 --> 00:09:09,435
Beautiful girls like you don't
usually go for guys like me.

158
00:09:09,435 --> 00:09:10,268
- Why not?

159
00:09:14,930 --> 00:09:18,847
- Well I mean I'm not as
handsome as some guys.

160
00:09:20,241 --> 00:09:21,074
- Come on.

161
00:09:21,984 --> 00:09:24,992
- Hey, I thought you were hungry?

162
00:09:24,992 --> 00:09:25,825
- Come on.

163
00:09:30,966 --> 00:09:32,805
Don't worry so much.

164
00:09:32,805 --> 00:09:35,007
You can always get another steak.

165
00:09:35,007 --> 00:09:37,178
But a moon like that.

166
00:09:37,178 --> 00:09:40,428
- Yeah, only comes up once every night.

167
00:09:41,693 --> 00:09:43,884
- No, it'll never be the same.

168
00:09:43,884 --> 00:09:45,830
Tomorrow it'll be different.

169
00:09:45,830 --> 00:09:47,377
- Why?

170
00:09:47,377 --> 00:09:48,960
- We won't be here.

171
00:09:49,938 --> 00:09:51,907
- We could come back.

172
00:09:51,907 --> 00:09:53,470
- But then we'd be different.

173
00:09:53,470 --> 00:09:54,303
- How so?

174
00:09:55,497 --> 00:09:59,080
- After tonight, we'll
always be different.

175
00:10:00,047 --> 00:10:02,916
- You always say the first
thing that pops into your head?

176
00:10:02,916 --> 00:10:06,026
- My husband used to ask
me the same question.

177
00:10:06,026 --> 00:10:07,926
- You've been married?

178
00:10:07,926 --> 00:10:09,343
- We're divorced.

179
00:10:10,283 --> 00:10:12,748
Jimmy was a nice boy, really sweet.

180
00:10:12,748 --> 00:10:14,581
But we were too young.

181
00:10:16,638 --> 00:10:18,531
I think my father had a concession stand

182
00:10:18,531 --> 00:10:20,281
down there somewhere.

183
00:10:24,477 --> 00:10:26,276
- You don't know?

184
00:10:26,276 --> 00:10:29,015
- I never really met him.

185
00:10:29,015 --> 00:10:32,496
He left the night before I was born.

186
00:10:32,496 --> 00:10:34,500
Mom and me, we moved around some.

187
00:10:34,500 --> 00:10:38,213
Sometimes I had to live in foster homes.

188
00:10:38,213 --> 00:10:39,839
But when mama was cutting films,

189
00:10:39,839 --> 00:10:40,899
we got to be together.

190
00:10:40,899 --> 00:10:42,297
- Well maybe I know her.

191
00:10:42,297 --> 00:10:44,865
Where's she working these days?

192
00:10:44,865 --> 00:10:46,503
- Remember what I said.

193
00:10:46,503 --> 00:10:50,055
I said we'd be different after tonight.

194
00:10:50,055 --> 00:10:52,722
- How are we gonna be different?

195
00:10:54,497 --> 00:10:55,997
- Can't you guess?

196
00:11:02,056 --> 00:11:04,556
(sultry jazz)

197
00:11:22,514 --> 00:11:24,736
- Norma Jean, this is a public beach.

198
00:11:24,736 --> 00:11:26,003
- Relax Ibsen.

199
00:11:26,003 --> 00:11:27,420
- My name is Bob.

200
00:11:39,994 --> 00:11:41,169
- [Norma] Come on in, Bob.

201
00:11:41,169 --> 00:11:42,502
Don't be afraid.

202
00:11:43,365 --> 00:11:44,427
C'mon!

203
00:11:44,427 --> 00:11:47,007
You know how to get undressed don't you?

204
00:11:47,007 --> 00:11:49,092
- Norma Jean, I don't
know if I can do this.

205
00:11:49,092 --> 00:11:52,953
- [Norma] If you don't,
you'll always be sorry.

206
00:11:52,953 --> 00:11:53,786
Come on, Bobby.

207
00:11:53,786 --> 00:11:55,786
Do it once, just for me.

208
00:12:10,759 --> 00:12:12,436
- [Bob] Incredible, isn't it?

209
00:12:12,436 --> 00:12:14,342
But I swear it's true.

210
00:12:14,342 --> 00:12:17,086
That was my first date with Norma Jean.

211
00:12:17,086 --> 00:12:18,760
Of course I didn't want it to end but,

212
00:12:18,760 --> 00:12:21,510
sooner or later, everything ends.

213
00:12:32,103 --> 00:12:34,274
You want me to leave you here?

214
00:12:34,274 --> 00:12:36,359
- I live with my aunt over there.

215
00:12:36,359 --> 00:12:38,296
She gets upset when I'm out late.

216
00:12:38,296 --> 00:12:41,129
I don't want her to hear your car.

217
00:12:52,050 --> 00:12:54,865
- Well, if you need me, I'm staying

218
00:12:54,865 --> 00:12:57,364
at the Hollywood Roosevelt Hotel.

219
00:12:57,364 --> 00:12:58,254
You can call me any time you want.

220
00:12:58,254 --> 00:12:59,337
Day or night.

221
00:13:16,848 --> 00:13:18,103
- Always a gentleman?

222
00:13:18,103 --> 00:13:18,936
- Try.

223
00:13:20,764 --> 00:13:24,847
- Better warn you. I may
not see you for a while.

224
00:13:25,915 --> 00:13:28,250
My moods can change pretty fast.

225
00:13:28,250 --> 00:13:30,583
I may not like you tomorrow.

226
00:13:32,121 --> 00:13:34,954
- Well then thank you for tonight.

227
00:13:42,754 --> 00:13:46,337
- Then again, tomorrow
maybe I'll love you.

228
00:13:53,805 --> 00:13:55,358
- [Aunt Dana] This is no hour

229
00:13:55,358 --> 00:13:57,555
for a young lady to be coming home.

230
00:13:57,555 --> 00:13:59,797
Forgive me child, I'm old.

231
00:13:59,797 --> 00:14:01,602
I need my peace.

232
00:14:01,602 --> 00:14:04,398
Now you can go stay at a hotel tonight.

233
00:14:04,398 --> 00:14:06,824
